The paper discusses active inference, which is a concept that is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), systems and control (cs.SY), and robotics (cs.RO). The agent-based model described in the paper also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, followed by cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.SY, and cs.RO.
